<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 2:02AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHWESTERN
APPOMATTOX...NORTHERN CAMPBELL...EAST CENTRAL BEDFORD... AND
SOUTHEASTERN AMHERST COUNTIES AND THE CITY OF LYNCHBURG THROUGH 230
AM EDT...
At 202 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Timberlake, or over Forest, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lynchburg...
Appomattox...
Bent Creek...
Concord...
Forest...
Rustburg...
and Madison Heights.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM EDT for
west central Virginia.</instruction>
